features: DeepCool CK560 PC case was designed following the latest PC component requirements to create an high-airflow gaming case without being too bulky which widely supports motherboards E-ATX, ATX, Micro-ATX and Mini-ITX

CK560 features cross pattern on the front panel to maximize ventilation in the gaming case, quick-release design makes the front panel can be easily removed from the case and mounted back to the position with the magnets and bottom hooks

High-compatibility CK560 ATX gaming case is compatible with 360mm AIO radiator on front or 280mm radiator on top, meanwhile, maximum 175mm CPU air cooler height limitation offers more choices for mighty dual-tower cooler with 140mm fans like DeepCool Assassin III

DeepCool CK560 PC case has an efficient cooling system thanks to the pre-installed three front ARGB fans and a 140mm rear non-ARGB fan which allows ample airflow, CK560 supports up to 6pcs 120mm or 5pcs 140mm fans to build High-airflow wind channel in the gaming case

DeepCool CK560 gaming case maximize potential with flexible configurations of any system setup, which supports PSU up to 160mm and 380mm GPUs in length, meanwhile, an adjustable built-in GPU bracket provides extra support extra weight for graphics card to avoid sag

CK560 provides two adjustable 3.5" drive cages and two spots for 2.5" SSD drives, DeepCool has implemented a neat toolless method for attaching SSD drive, manually screwing the four metal studs on SSD drive and push it into the drive bay on the back board is all you need to do

Get more connectivity for your modern devices needing with CK560 modular front I/O ports, two USB 3.0 ports, a USB 3.1 Type-C port, a combo audio jack and a reset button is settled in the gaming case for better using experience

To build a minimal PC style, DeepCool CK560 carries high-quality rubber grommets in the gaming case and a bag of zip ties to improve cable management in the steel panel side with big cable space about 2cm height clearance

DeepCool CK560 gaming case features with a removable front mesh filter underneath the solid front panel, the dust filters on top and bottom of the PC case are detachable as well for easy cleaning when it’s necessary

Magnetic tempered glass side panel on DeepCool CK560 PC case offers the most convenient way to mount with ease, an optional safety lock is featured for extra security to protect the glass panel from accidentally knock and crash during transport

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Winning Combination of Style and Performance
reviews.reviewText: I recently had the pleasure of building my new gaming rig using the DeepCool CK560 PC Case, and I must say it has exceeded my expectations. The combination of its sleek design and high-airflow front panel made the entire building process both visually appealing and efficient.Design:The first thing that caught my eye was the CK560's modern and stylish design. The case has a clean and minimalistic appearance, with a tempered glass side panel that showcases the components inside. The black finish gives it a premium look, making it a perfect fit for any gaming setup.Build Quality:The build quality of the CK560 is impressive. The materials used feel robust, and the case itself has a sturdy construction. The side panels are easy to remove and reattach, allowing for a hassle-free installation process. The attention to detail is evident, and it's clear that DeepCool prioritized both aesthetics and functionality.Airflow:One of the standout features of the CK560 is its high-airflow front panel. The strategically designed mesh allows for optimal airflow, keeping my components cool during intense gaming sessions. This is crucial for maintaining performance and ensuring the longevity of the hardware. The case supports multiple fan configurations, providing flexibility for users who want to customize their cooling setup.Ease of Building:Building inside the CK560 was a breeze. The spacious interior provided ample room for cable management, and the well-placed cutouts made it easy to route cables neatly. The tool-free drive bays and removable dust filters added to the overall convenience of the build process. It's evident that DeepCool considered the user experience when designing this case.In conclusion, the DeepCool CK560 ATX PC Case is a fantastic choice for anyone looking to build a stylish and high-performance gaming rig. Its combination of aesthetics, build quality, and airflow make it a standout in its class. Whether you're a seasoned PC builder or a first-timer, the CK560 offers a satisfying and enjoyable building experience. I highly recommend it to anyone in the market for a reliable and visually appealing PC case.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very impressed for the price
reviews.reviewText: Just finished building in this case and I have to say that I am very happy with it. For $90 I can't imagine getting something better.Pros: - Everything is very intuitive. I didn't even need to look at instruction book once.- The aesthetic design is great. Not too flashy but not boring at all.- Materials feel good. Maybe not the highest quality but definitely sturdy enough. Nothing feels like it will break.- Includes 3 ARGB fans and 1 regular 140mm fan. I didn't even realize it was a 140 until I started building in it. All work great.- Cable management space is deceptively large. I didn't really have any issues trying to fit all the cables. By removing the HDD drive cage, the bottom chamber has a ton of extra room for cable management.- I like how easy the front panel comes off. It's just a magnet. Somehow it's easy to remove but also feels secure in place. It also looks pretty cool.- The temps are great. It doesn't look like the most airflow centric cases out there but it definitely is.Cons: - The back panel can be annoying to fit back on once the cables are routed. The front panel has little teeth at the bottom to latch and slide into place. For whatever reason the back doesn't have that. Not too bad, though.- The top IO RGB bottom doesn't allow for static colors. Only a few select dynamic effects. If you want more control over the RGB then plug them into your motherboard or a RGB controller. The fans do daisy chain so it's not a huge deal.- Not the quietest case but nowhere near the worst.- Can't fit a 360mm AIO at the top. This case is a little smaller than other mid tower cases. If you want to use a 360mm then you'll have to replace the included front fans and put it there. If you put a 280mm at the top, route all your motherboard and fan cables first or it'll be too cramped to do so.If you're looking for a case in this price range I can vouch that you wouldn't be disappointed with this. Easily worth more than the $90 I spent. If you're trying to decide between this one and another case, just go with this one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 20, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Compact Case with aRGB fans.
reviews.reviewText: This budget friendly case is awesome if you are looking for a compact ATX tower. Enough space for my RX-6900XT and with room to spare when I get my water cooling parts. Clean black interior really helps to height light the components and addressable RGB fans make this case a great value. I paired the case with a DeepCool PQ1000M 1000w compact power supply and I was surprised how easy it was to cable manage the all the power cables.The Fans are pretty bright. I plan to add more DeepCool aRGB fans when I mount a 240mm radiator in the next couple of months. The tempered glass side makes the case very classy!! Definitely an easy but understated build in IMHO. Love my new ALL AMD BUILD!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 25, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not Bad For A Budget Buy
reviews.reviewText: I bought this 3 weeks ago. I didn't want to just replace my case, I needed to make sure it had room for my SATA drives and my SSD. The plan now is to slowly upgrade. A new PSU was installed when I got the case now I am getting ready to buy a GPU and am also swapping out the rear 140mm fan for a white RGB. Unfortunately, the 3080 I have my eye on is an exact fit and that does not bode well. Back to the drawing board. Push comes to shove I'll probably get a 3070 or 3070 Ti. Anyway, it's a decent case for a budget buy. That said I would have liked for it to have more USB ports and I no longer hear a beep on startup and it doesn't have that startup/reboot/reset light. Still, it's not enough for me to return it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Very nice case, fairly easy to build in. I ended up using 3 FC 120 fans for the front intake. I may use the 3 included fans in another build, or place 2 at the top.The case looks very nice, no rattles and feels pretty sturdy. I bypassed the led button, but I see where that could be pretty cool if you were to use the included fans.All and all I really like it and I think it turned out great.

reviews.reviewTitle: Gabinete con buena circulación de aire
reviews.reviewText: Por lo único que no le estoy dando 5 estrellas, es por qué me llegó con un tornillo doblado de la placa donde se pone el vidrio templado y cuesta un poco volver a poner la parte de vidrio templado por lo mismo.En si el gabinete tiene buen espacio para poner cualquier tipo de componentes y con los ventiladores preinstalados hace más fácil el armado de la computadora, me ha ayudado a mantener buenas temperaturas en mis componentes y la verdad estoy impresionado ya que el lugar donde vivo es un lugar donde hace demasiado calor.

Ho acquistato il prodotto da Amazon Warehouse come "in ottime condizioni". Era stato provato dal precedente acquirente ma le condizioni erano come indicate in descrizione. Mancavano gli accessori.Il prodotto è di buona qualità, le lamiere non sono particolarmente spesse e tendono a flettere, il fianco sinistro è in vetro e permette di vedere l'interno del computer. Sono presenti filtri per la polvere rimovibili per una facile pulizia.Ottima la connettività anteriore con porte usb c e usb 3.Ho contattato il supporto DeepCool per avere gli accessori mancanti, in particolare mi facevano comodo le viti di supporto dei dischi da 2,5" e il cavetto per collegare le ventole RGB alla scheda madre: con un veloce scambio di email ho spiegato il problema e nel giro di 20gg mi è stato recapitato tutto a casa dalla Cina.Quindi supporto ottimo.Lo consiglio per il rapporto prezzo/qualità.
Lieferung war pünktlich und gut verpackt. Alles dabei was man braucht und sieht dazu super aus, top Qualität. Mir gefällt es richtig gut

Fantastico case middle tower.Leggero compatto e spazioso, ottime finiture e 4 ventole (3 rgb) preinstallate.Vi consiglio questo rispetto al fratello minore CG560 perché ha il frontale magnetico rimovibile, porta type c e supporto per gpu veramente comodo e ben fatto.Questa volta Deepcool si è superata!

ottimo case di qualità, migliore di tanti altri che fanno sembrare qualcosa di nuovo, ma alla fine di nuovo non cè nulla, la DeepCool CK560 ormai è il top in ogni componente hardware, qualità dei materiali, e sopra tutto assistenza. Cosa voliamo di piu'. Del case non vi parlo guardate le foto e rendevi conto di che livello è questo hardware, meraviglioso.
